During the LibSass and Ruby Sass years, I published a set of small pure-Sass
libraries (mostly prefixed “Sassy”) for everything from list helpers to a JSON
parser. They were experiments in what you could squeeze out of the language
before `@use` and the modern module system reshaped how Sass is written.

Each library lives in its own repository; this page groups them so the
[projects list](/projects/) stays readable.

- [SassyBitwise](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyBitwise): Bitwise operators implemented in Sass as an experiment, co-authored with [Valérian Galliat](https://github.com/valeriangalliat).
- [SassyCast](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyCast): Functions to convert between Sass types (numbers, colors, strings, lists, maps, and more).
- [SassyGradients](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyGradients): A thin API over CSS linear and radial gradients to make them easier to use.
- [SassyIteratorsGenerators](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyIteratorsGenerators): Iterators and generators in Sass.
- [SassyJSON](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyJSON): A partial JSON encoder and decoder in Sass — useful mainly as a proof of concept and for tooling experiments.
- [SassyLists](https://github.com/at-import/SassyLists): Helpers for chunking, looping, serializing, debugging lists, and more.
- [SassyLogger](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyLogger): A logging mixin and levels so Sass builds could emit structured messages during compilation.
- [SassyMatrix](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyMatrix): 2D matrix operations and helpers built on Sass lists and maps.
- [SassySort](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassySort): Several classic sorting algorithms implemented as Sass functions — more fun than production advice.
- [SassyStrings](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyStrings): String manipulation helpers to complement what the language offered at the time.
- [SassyTester](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/SassyTester): A minimal harness for asserting Sass function output in the pre–module-system world.
- [Sass Semver](https://github.com/KittyGiraudel/sass-semver): A small Semantic Versioning parser in Sass.

{% callout "warning" %}
A lot of these libraries were largely authored as proof-of-concepts and experimental playgrounds. Your typical project shouldn’t need any of this, especially as the language and its ecosystem matured with the years.
{% endcallout %}
